{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"tree":1},[2,26,45,59],{"slug":3,"title":4,"pages":5},"start","Start",[6,14,20],{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":8,"path":9,"title":10,"description":11,"order":12,"verified":13},"claw","install","/content/claw/docs/start/install.md","Install","Get the NullClaw binary via Homebrew, Docker, or a source build with Zig 0.16.0.",1,"v2026.5.29",{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":15,"path":16,"title":17,"description":18,"order":19,"verified":13},"quickstart","/content/claw/docs/start/quickstart.md","Quickstart","From a fresh install to a first conversation and a running gateway.",2,{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":21,"path":22,"title":23,"description":24,"order":25,"verified":13},"first-channel","/content/claw/docs/start/first-channel.md","Your first channel","Connect NullClaw to Telegram (or any of the 26 channels) and lock it down with allowlists.",3,{"slug":27,"title":28,"pages":29},"configure","Configure",[30,35,40],{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":31,"path":32,"title":33,"description":34,"order":12,"verified":13},"configuration","/content/claw/docs/configure/configuration.md","Configuration","One JSON file at ~/.nullclaw/config.json — OpenClaw-compatible, snake_case, no magic.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":36,"path":37,"title":38,"description":39,"order":19,"verified":13},"providers","/content/claw/docs/configure/providers.md","Providers","Connect ~60 model providers, set the default route, and add fallbacks and auto-routing.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":41,"path":42,"title":43,"description":44,"order":25,"verified":13},"memory","/content/claw/docs/configure/memory.md","Memory","Hybrid search over SQLite by default, nine other engines when you need them, and CLI tools to keep it clean.",{"slug":46,"title":47,"pages":48},"operate","Operate",[49,54],{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":50,"path":51,"title":52,"description":53,"order":12,"verified":13},"gateway-and-service","/content/claw/docs/operate/gateway-and-service.md","Gateway and service","Run NullClaw long-term — the HTTP gateway, pairing, cron endpoints, and background service mode.",{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":55,"path":56,"title":57,"description":58,"order":19,"verified":13},"security","/content/claw/docs/operate/security.md","Security","The layers NullClaw enforces by default, the settings that widen them, and how to audit for leaked secrets.",{"slug":60,"title":61,"pages":62},"reference","Reference",[63],{"siteId":7,"section":60,"slug":64,"path":65,"title":66,"description":67,"order":12,"verified":13},"cli","/content/claw/docs/reference/cli.md","CLI reference","Every nullclaw command, grouped by task — setup, runtime, channels, cron, memory, automation flags, and build flags."],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"doc":1,"raw":10,"dateModified":35,"sectionTitle":36,"prev":37,"next":45},{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":4,"path":5,"title":6,"description":7,"order":8,"verified":9,"body":10,"html":11,"toc":12},"claw","configure","configuration","/content/claw/docs/configure/configuration.md","Configuration","One JSON file at ~/.nullclaw/config.json — OpenClaw-compatible, snake_case, no magic.",1,"v2026.5.29","\nEverything NullClaw does is driven by a single JSON file. `nullclaw onboard` creates it; you edit it; the runtime reads it. There is no second source of truth.\n\n## Where it lives\n\n| Platform | Path |\n| --- | --- |\n| macOS / Linux | `~/.nullclaw/config.json` |\n| Windows | `%USERPROFILE%\\.nullclaw\\config.json` |\n| Docker | `/nullclaw-data/config.json` |\n\nThe structure is OpenClaw-compatible: snake_case keys, providers under `models.providers`, the default model under `agents.defaults.model.primary`, channels wrapped in `accounts`. Top-level `default_provider` / `default_model` keys are **not** supported.\n\n## A minimal working config\n\nEnough for local CLI mode — replace the API key:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"openrouter\": { \"api_key\": \"YOUR_OPENROUTER_API_KEY\" }\n    }\n  },\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"model\": { \"primary\": \"openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\" }\n    }\n  },\n  \"channels\": { \"cli\": true },\n  \"memory\": { \"backend\": \"sqlite\", \"auto_save\": true },\n  \"gateway\": { \"host\": \"127.0.0.1\", \"port\": 3000, \"require_pairing\": true },\n  \"autonomy\": { \"level\": \"supervised\", \"workspace_only\": true, \"max_actions_per_hour\": 20 },\n  \"security\": {\n    \"sandbox\": { \"backend\": \"auto\" },\n    \"audit\": { \"enabled\": true }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## The main sections\n\n| Section | What it controls |\n| --- | --- |\n| `models.providers` | Provider credentials and endpoints — see [Providers](/docs/configure/providers/) |\n| `agents.defaults` | Default model route, heartbeat interval |\n| `agents.list` | Named agent profiles for delegation and routing, each with optional `system_prompt` and `workspace_path` |\n| `channels` | Messaging channels and their allowlists — see [Your first channel](/docs/start/first-channel/) |\n| `memory` | Backend, embeddings, hybrid-search weights — see [Memory](/docs/configure/memory/) |\n| `gateway` | Bind address, port, pairing, body limits |\n| `autonomy` | Autonomy level, workspace scoping, command allowlists, rate limits |\n| `security` | Sandbox backend, resource limits, audit log |\n| `mcp_servers` | MCP servers over stdio or HTTP |\n| `bindings` | Route specific chats or Telegram forum topics to named agents |\n| `reliability` | Provider retries, backoff, fallback providers and models |\n| `a2a` | Agent-to-agent protocol endpoints |\n\n## Values are literal\n\nNullClaw does not expand `${VAR}` inside `config.json` strings — including custom header values. If you need environment-based secrets, render the file ahead of time with your own tooling, or use the `~/.nullclaw/service-env` hook in service mode (see [Gateway and service](/docs/operate/gateway-and-service/)).\n\nA few settings do come from the environment at runtime: `NULLCLAW_PORT`, `NULLCLAW_BIND`, `NULLCLAW_WORKSPACE`, `NULLCLAW_WEB_TOKEN`, `NULLCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN`, and web-search keys such as `BRAVE_API_KEY` or `TAVILY_API_KEY`.\n\n## Reading and reloading\n\nInspect the effective config from the CLI:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw config show --json            # the full on-disk config\nnullclaw config get gateway.port      # one dotted value\n```\n\nInside `nullclaw agent`, `/config reload` hot-reloads supported keys — including agent profiles — without restarting. After bigger edits, restart and verify:\n\n```bash\nnullclaw doctor\nnullclaw status\nnullclaw channel status\n```\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Pre-1.0: config and CLI may change between releases. The repo ships `config.example.json` — compare against it when a startup error points at config.\n\n## Binding chats to agents\n\nNamed profiles in `agents.list` can be routed per chat or per Telegram forum topic. The quick way is the `/bind \u003Cagent>` command inside the target chat; NullClaw persists an exact `bindings[]` entry to config. Topic-specific bindings win over a group fallback by route priority — order in the array does not matter. `/bind status` shows the effective route; `/bind clear` removes the exact binding.\n\n## Next\n\nTune models in [Providers](/docs/configure/providers/), or pick a memory engine in [Memory](/docs/configure/memory/).\n","\u003Cp>Everything NullClaw does is driven by a single JSON file. \u003Ccode>nullclaw onboard\u003C/code> creates it; you edit it; the runtime reads it. There is no second source of truth.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"where-it-lives\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-where-it-lives\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-where-it-lives\">Where it lives\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#where-it-lives\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Where it lives\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"table-scroll\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Data table: Platform, Path\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ctable>\n\u003Cthead>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Cth>Platform\u003C/th>\n\u003Cth>Path\u003C/th>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/thead>\n\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>macOS / Linux\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>~/.nullclaw/config.json\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>Windows\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>%USERPROFILE%\\.nullclaw\\config.json\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>Docker\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>/nullclaw-data/config.json\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/tbody>\n\u003C/table>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>The structure is OpenClaw-compatible: snake_case keys, providers under \u003Ccode>models.providers\u003C/code>, the default model under \u003Ccode>agents.defaults.model.primary\u003C/code>, channels wrapped in \u003Ccode>accounts\u003C/code>. Top-level \u003Ccode>default_provider\u003C/code> / \u003Ccode>default_model\u003C/code> keys are \u003Cstrong>not\u003C/strong> supported.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"a-minimal-working-config\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-a-minimal-working-config\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-a-minimal-working-config\">A minimal working config\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#a-minimal-working-config\" aria-label=\"Permalink to A minimal working config\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Enough for local CLI mode — replace the API key:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"json\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">{\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">models\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">providers\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">openrouter\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">api_key\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"YOUR_OPENROUTER_API_KEY\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">agents\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">defaults\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">primary\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">channels\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">cli\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> true\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">memory\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">backend\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"sqlite\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">auto_save\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> true\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">gateway\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">host\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"127.0.0.1\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">port\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> 3000\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">require_pairing\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> true\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">autonomy\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">level\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"supervised\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">workspace_only\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> true\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">max_actions_per_hour\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> 20\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">security\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">sandbox\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">backend\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"auto\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">audit\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">enabled\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> true\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"the-main-sections\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-the-main-sections\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-the-main-sections\">The main sections\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#the-main-sections\" aria-label=\"Permalink to The main sections\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"table-scroll\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Data table: Section, What it controls\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ctable>\n\u003Cthead>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Cth>Section\u003C/th>\n\u003Cth>What it controls\u003C/th>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/thead>\n\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>models.providers\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Provider credentials and endpoints — see \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/providers/\">Providers\u003C/a>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>agents.defaults\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Default model route, heartbeat interval\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>agents.list\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Named agent profiles for delegation and routing, each with optional \u003Ccode>system_prompt\u003C/code> and \u003Ccode>workspace_path\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>channels\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Messaging channels and their allowlists — see \u003Ca href=\"/docs/start/first-channel/\">Your first channel\u003C/a>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>memory\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Backend, embeddings, hybrid-search weights — see \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/memory/\">Memory\u003C/a>\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>gateway\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Bind address, port, pairing, body limits\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>autonomy\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Autonomy level, workspace scoping, command allowlists, rate limits\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>security\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Sandbox backend, resource limits, audit log\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>mcp_servers\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>MCP servers over stdio or HTTP\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>bindings\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Route specific chats or Telegram forum topics to named agents\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>reliability\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Provider retries, backoff, fallback providers and models\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>a2a\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Agent-to-agent protocol endpoints\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/tbody>\n\u003C/table>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"values-are-literal\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-values-are-literal\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-values-are-literal\">Values are literal\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#values-are-literal\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Values are literal\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>NullClaw does not expand \u003Ccode>${VAR}\u003C/code> inside \u003Ccode>config.json\u003C/code> strings — including custom header values. If you need environment-based secrets, render the file ahead of time with your own tooling, or use the \u003Ccode>~/.nullclaw/service-env\u003C/code> hook in service mode (see \u003Ca href=\"/docs/operate/gateway-and-service/\">Gateway and service\u003C/a>).\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>A few settings do come from the environment at runtime: \u003Ccode>NULLCLAW_PORT\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>NULLCLAW_BIND\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>NULLCLAW_WORKSPACE\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>NULLCLAW_WEB_TOKEN\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>NULLCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN\u003C/code>, and web-search keys such as \u003Ccode>BRAVE_API_KEY\u003C/code> or \u003Ccode>TAVILY_API_KEY\u003C/code>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"reading-and-reloading\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-reading-and-reloading\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-reading-and-reloading\">Reading and reloading\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#reading-and-reloading\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Reading and reloading\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Inspect the effective config from the CLI:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> config\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> show\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> --json\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">            # the full on-disk config\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> config\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> get\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> gateway.port\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">      # one dotted value\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Inside \u003Ccode>nullclaw agent\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>/config reload\u003C/code> hot-reloads supported keys — including agent profiles — without restarting. After bigger edits, restart and verify:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> doctor\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> status\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> channel\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> status\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Caside class=\"callout callout--note\">\u003Cdiv class=\"callout-title\">Note\u003C/div>\u003Cp>Pre-1.0: config and CLI may change between releases. The repo ships \u003Ccode>config.example.json\u003C/code> — compare against it when a startup error points at config.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/aside>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"binding-chats-to-agents\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-binding-chats-to-agents\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-binding-chats-to-agents\">Binding chats to agents\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#binding-chats-to-agents\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Binding chats to agents\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Named profiles in \u003Ccode>agents.list\u003C/code> can be routed per chat or per Telegram forum topic. The quick way is the \u003Ccode>/bind &lt;agent&gt;\u003C/code> command inside the target chat; NullClaw persists an exact \u003Ccode>bindings[]\u003C/code> entry to config. Topic-specific bindings win over a group fallback by route priority — order in the array does not matter. \u003Ccode>/bind status\u003C/code> shows the effective route; \u003Ccode>/bind clear\u003C/code> removes the exact binding.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"next\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-next\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-next\">Next\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#next\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Next\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Tune models in \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/providers/\">Providers\u003C/a>, or pick a memory engine in \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/memory/\">Memory\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>\n",[13,17,20,23,26,29,32],{"id":14,"text":15,"depth":16},"where-it-lives","Where it lives",2,{"id":18,"text":19,"depth":16},"a-minimal-working-config","A minimal working config",{"id":21,"text":22,"depth":16},"the-main-sections","The main sections",{"id":24,"text":25,"depth":16},"values-are-literal","Values are literal",{"id":27,"text":28,"depth":16},"reading-and-reloading","Reading and reloading",{"id":30,"text":31,"depth":16},"binding-chats-to-agents","Binding chats to agents",{"id":33,"text":34,"depth":16},"next","Next","2026-07-16","Configure",{"siteId":2,"section":38,"slug":39,"path":40,"title":41,"description":42,"order":43,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":44},"start","first-channel","/content/claw/docs/start/first-channel.md","Your first channel","Connect NullClaw to Telegram (or any of the 26 channels) and lock it down with allowlists.",3,"Start",{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":46,"path":47,"title":48,"description":49,"order":16,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":36},"providers","/content/claw/docs/configure/providers.md","Providers","Connect ~60 model providers, set the default route, and add fallbacks and auto-routing."],"uses":{"params":["section","slug"]}}]}
